postcontent: EXPS 3-0 NIB with Night Vision for sale. Bought on April 11, 2013 and received a week later but found that I already have the same exact model. I thought my first one was EXPS-2 but it turned out to be EXPS-3 as well, so I  am selling the one I just bought. Got it from Bass Pro Shop online and now it's unavailable anywhere, selling at purchase price with receipt. Never registered, never used.   This is the fastest way to acquire a sight picture for initial and follow up shots, a staple in competitive shooting.  The EXPS is better than the XPS because the built in QD mount raises the EXPS 7 mm so it eliminates the need for an extra riser mount yet still allow a lower 1/3 co-witness, also the controls are locared at the side instead of the back for much easier use especillay if you plan on having a magnifier behind it.  EXPS-2 is not night vision compatible which is important for night competitions and hunting.  EXPS is the best sight for Close Quarter shooting but is also good for long distance up to 500 yards with a cheap 3x magnifer, I use PA.

title: For Sale:  FR8 Rifle - 7.62 NATO caliber, with original bayonet & sling
postcontent:
This FR8 rifle is in excellent condition with a pristine bore. Reciever & bolt numbers match. Here is some info on this very collectible rifle:

History:
The FR7 and FR8 were introduced in the 1950s when the Spanish military was already implementing the CETME automatic rifle, but did not yet have sufficient inventory to equip and train all troops. The rifles were made from existing stockpiles of Mauser bolt-action rifles, the FR-7 from the rifle model 1919 Santa Barbara and the FR-8 from the 1943 Santa Barbara carbine. They were adjusted to the new NATO calibre 7.62×51mm, and being of a suitably compact built, the FR 8 was used well into the 1970s by mounted Guardia Civil units in the Sierra Nevada (Spain).

Features:
The flash hider was designed to be compatible with NATO standard rifle grenades. The under-barrel tube, which resembles the gas cylinder found on automatic weapons, actually serves as the bayonet mount and as storage for cleaning gear. The rear sight is a diopter elevation-adjustable rotary type with aperatures for 200m, 300m, & 400m as well as an open "V" notch for 100m. Operation is identical to the standard Mauser design.

Price is $500. FTF only with pickup in the Valrico/Brandon area. You must be a FL resident & 21 or older to purchase.

Please text or call 585-754-2seven2eight... Your viewing an FN Herstal Forty-Nine 40 cal. S&W... This is a beautiful pistol which includes the breach lock, original box and 2 Ten round magazines. New York State Pistol Permit holders only transfer to be done at local FFL (can ship out of state to your local FFL)... Will consider reasonable offers.  

The FN Forty-Nine is a recoil operated, locked breech semi-automatic pistol developed by the Belgium company Fabrique Nationale (FN). The Forty-Nine uses an improved linkless locking principle intended for police use. The pistol is striker fired and uses FN's Repeatable Secure Striker mechanism.[2] This means that unlike many other striker-fired pistols, such as the Glock family, the Forty-Nine operates on a double-action only (DAO) trigger mechanism, meaning that the hammer is cocked by the trigger pull before every shot. This allows the user to re-strike a misfired cartridge simply by pulling the trigger again.[1] The Forty-Nine has no external (manual) safety switches. The double-stacked detachable magazine holds sixteen rounds in 9mm caliber and fourteen in .40 S&W. The frame is constructed of polymer and the slide of stainless steel. An accessory rail under the barrel allows for quick and easy mounting of laser aiming modules and flashlights.

title: For Sale:  KEL-TEC RFB 308 BULLPUP 7.62
postcontent:
KEL-TEC RFB NEW UNFIRED CONDITION.RFB RFB stands for Rifle, Forward-ejecting Bullpup. Why forward-ejecting? Because it allows the RFB to be the first truly ambidextrous 7.62 NATO Bullpup ever developed. The patented, dual-extractor system maintains control of the case from the moment it leaves the magazine and upon firing, pulls the fired case from the chamber and lifts them to push them into an ejection chute above the barrel, where they exit. The Bullpup configuration and tilting-block mechanism allow the 18" model to be only 26.1" long, or as much as 14" shorter in overall length than its competitors with equal barrel lengths. Furthermore, the stock and mechanism cross-section is similar to a conventional rifle, in stark contrast to existing Bullpup rifles. The RFB is also the safest Bullpup ever developed because the breech is separated from the shooters face by two layers of 1.6 mm steel. In the highly unlikely event of a case rupture, gas expansion is directed downwards through the magazine well to protect the shooters head and face. TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS Calibers: 308 nato Weight unloaded (no magazine): 8.1 lbs Length: 26" Barrel length: 18" Magazine: 10 or 20 or 30 FAL Practical range: 1200m 600m The RFB is a short-stroke gas piston operated semi-automatic rifle in 7.62 mm NATO caliber. It accepts standard metric FAL type magazines which work "drop free" and do not need to be tilted in. Five 30 round DS magazines and one 20 round magazine is included*. Barrels on current models are 18" and 24” long, with Salt Bath Nitride Finish in the bore and chamber. All of the barrels are now SBN (Salt Bath Nitride) for finish as it will last longer than the previous chrome-lining finish and the bolts are now finished with Titanium Nitride to assist with the smoothness of operation. The muzzle is threaded 5/8x24 TPI and comes equipped with Vortex Flash Hider*, except the Hunter Variant which comes with a thread protector. All controls are fully ambidextrous; the reciprocating operating handle can be switched to either side. The trigger mechanism is second to no other Bullpup ever built and better than nearly all commercial semi-auto rifles. The safety disconnects the trigger and blocks the hammer action. A Mil-Spec Picatinny rail is attached rigidly to the barrel. Folding iron sights are provided, allowing the user to select from the very best new optics and sight systems available. The RFB comes with a two point sling that can be easily configured to suit the user's preference. Available accessories include a free-floating, Quad Rail Picatinny and Sight Riser, bipod mounts, a removable bayonet lug for use with NATO style bayonets including M9 Bayonet, Stock Spacers for added length, and a Tactical Operation Handle.

The 44 barrel is what came on this pistol. The pistol itself will take barrels from .41 to .44 caliber. I trade! I trade for scrap gold, gold coins, silver coins and other guns. Please contact me before bidding only if you have never purchased on armslist. If you buy something from me on armslist and do not pay for it I must report you as a non-paying bidder in order to get my money back for the sale and I will leave you negative feedback so keep your word. If you have ever been a non-paying bidder or intend to be one, DO NOT BID! We accept trade-ins as well as scrap gold for payment. Shipping is flat rate of 34.00 for handguns and 39.00 for long guns shipped Priority Mail, Insured to lower 48 in a new ace soft case. If you feel there is no need for insurance you may subtract $5.00 from the shipping price. All guns ship USPS. Email any question: sharonweaver@rocketmail.com. We prefer payment through postal money orders or cashier's checks. ABSOLUTELY NO WESTERN UNION MONEY ORDERS, they gladly write them but no one cashes them, and no international checks or international money orders. Hawaii and Alaska shipping is 69.00 flat. Once bidding begins, auction must go on. I pride myself in getting things shipped out to you guys as soon as payment and ffl is received. I ship on Tuesdays and Thursdays so if payment comes in late Thursday your gun won't ship until Tuesday. I also shoot every gun either before I post the add or before I ship to make sure there are no problems with ammo feeding or any other problem unless the caliber is rare in which case I may not have the ammo needed to fire it.
